[?2004huser@d34482275169:~/scheduler$ cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'
[?2004l[?2004h> # Scheduler Bug Fix Summary
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Problem
[?2004l[?2004h> The meeting reminder application was sending reminders at incorrect times for meetings between 2am-3am local time (Europe/Berlin), with exactly 1 hour offset. M[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[C[K.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Root Cause
[?2004l[?2004h> In `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # BUGGY CODE (line 28):
[?2004l[?2004h> utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
[?2004l[?2004h> berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)  # WRONG!
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> This code treated the parsed UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin timezone, rather than converting FROM UTC TO Berlin.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## The Fix
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # FIXED CODE:
